{
  "design_notes": "S0 introduces the beat with sparse kicks on the BAR lane and snares on NOTE, building familiarity with the 88 BPM tempo using simple downbeats before a brief sweep leads into the drop. S1 increases density during the high-energy drop, utilizing a steady BAR-kick backbone interspersed with quick GAP/NOTE snare alternations on 0.5-beat subdivisions to emulate synthwave propulsion. S2 guides the player through the outro wind-down, maintaining the core kick-and-snare flow but gradually spacing out the offbeat hits to let the rhythm breathe as the track resolves.",
